1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
One delivers instructions; the other delivers a piece of the pathogen.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:10,000
mRNA vaccines teach our cells how to fight an infection by delivering genetic instructions.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:14,800
Traditional vaccines, however, often use weakened or inactivated parts of the virus.

4
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:19,200
Studies suggest mRNA could be faster to develop than traditional methods.

5
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:22,800
But both types can effectively train our immune systems.

6
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,200
Ultimately, each platform has its advantages.

7
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,000
Understanding them helps us make informed choices.

